# breadforge environment variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Recommended: export in your shell profile (~/.zshrc / ~/.zprofile) so these
# are available regardless of the working directory.
#
#   export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
#   export BREADFORGE_GH_TOKEN=ghp_...
#
# Alternatively, copy this file to .env at your project root.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── Required ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Anthropic API key — used by the plan handler (SDK call) and all build agents.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here

# GitHub token for the yeast-bot service account.
# Required scopes: repo, workflow.
# Used to: authenticate build agents to GitHub, add yeast-bot as collaborator,
# accept repo invitations on behalf of yeast-bot.
BREADFORGE_GH_TOKEN=ghp_your-yeast-bot-token-here


# ── Core orchestrator settings ────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Default model for build agents (overrides assessor selection for all nodes).
# Accepted values: any Anthropic model ID or claude-opus-4-6 / claude-sonnet-4-6 / claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
# BREADFORGE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6

# Maximum number of graph nodes running in parallel.
# BREADFORGE_CONCURRENCY=3

# Minutes before a single agent subprocess is killed.
# BREADFORGE_AGENT_TIMEOUT_MINUTES=60

# Seconds between orchestrator watchdog scans (checks for stuck nodes).
# BREADFORGE_WATCHDOG_INTERVAL_SECONDS=60

# Maximum times a node is retried before being abandoned.
# BREADFORGE_MAX_RETRIES=3

# Root directory for bead JSON files.
# BREADFORGE_BEADS_DIR=~/.breadforge/beads


# ── Multi-backend routing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# breadforge can route research and plan nodes to non-Anthropic backends.
# Build nodes always use Claude (the claude CLI subprocess).

# Backend for research nodes.  Options: anthropic (default), gemini, openai.
# BREADFORGE_RESEARCH_BACKEND=anthropic

# Backend for plan nodes.  Options: anthropic (default), gemini, openai.
# BREADFORGE_PLAN_BACKEND=anthropic

# Model override for research nodes (uses backend default if unset).
# BREADFORGE_RESEARCH_MODEL=

# Model override for plan nodes (uses backend default if unset).
# BREADFORGE_PLAN_MODEL=

# Model override for build nodes via BackendRouter (uses assessor selection if unset).
# BREADFORGE_BUILD_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6

# Model override for design-doc nodes (uses backend default if unset).
# BREADFORGE_DESIGN_MODEL=


# ── Alternative backend API keys ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Only needed if BREADFORGE_RESEARCH_BACKEND or BREADFORGE_PLAN_BACKEND is set
# to the corresponding provider.

# OpenAI API key — required when backend=openai.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# Google AI (Gemini) API key — required when backend=gemini.
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=AIza...


# ── Credential proxy ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The credential proxy issues scoped tokens to build agents instead of passing
# raw API keys.  An ephemeral per-session key is generated if this is unset.

# HMAC signing key for credential proxy tokens.  Set a stable value to keep
# tokens valid across orchestrator restarts (e.g. during development).
# BREADFORGE_PROXY_SECRET=


# ── breadmin integration ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Path to the breadmin SQLite database used for cost tracking and run history.
# BREADMIN_DB_PATH=data/breadmin.db


# ── Internal (do not set manually) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# BREADFORGE_AGENT=1   — set automatically inside agent subprocesses to
#                         prevent recursive orchestrator nesting.
